    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, boil a full kettle and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>pasta</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-kyiv-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-lemony-courgette/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> into quarters</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped parsley</strong>, a squeeze of <strong>lemon </strong>juice<strong> </strong>and 25g <span class=\"text-purple\">[40g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[50g]</span><strong> butter</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic & herb butter</strong></p><p>Tip: Put the butter in the microwave for 10 secs if it's too cold to mix!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-kyiv-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-lemony-courgette/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and chop your<strong> courgette[s]</strong> in half lengthways, then into batons</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [420ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>soft cheese </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-kyiv-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-lemony-courgette/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> diced chicken </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 6-8 min or until golden</p><p>Once golden, remove the <strong>chicken</strong> and set aside, reserve the pan</p><p>Tip: It's okay if the chicken's a little pink on the inside, it'll cook more later!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-kyiv-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-lemony-courgette/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat and add 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>garlic & herb butter </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Once melted, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms</p><p>Gradually stir in the <strong>creamy stock</strong>, a little at a time (to prevent lumps forming)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-kyiv-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-lemony-courgette/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained pasta </strong>and <strong>chicken pieces</strong> to the pan with the <strong>creamy sauce </strong>and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> pasta mixture</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if its looking a little dry!</p><p>Transfer the <strong>pasta mixture</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>in a bowl with the <strong>remaining chopped parsley</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>\u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-kyiv-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-lemony-courgette/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Sprinkle the <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong> all over the pasta mixture</p><p>Dollop the <strong>remaining garlic & herb butter </strong>over the breadcrumbs and put the dish in the oven for 12-15 min or until golden and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken breast kyiv pasta bake</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>courgette batons </strong>to a baking tray with a squeeze of <strong>lemon</strong> juice, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until cooked through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-breast-kyiv-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-lemony-courgette/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chicken breast kyiv pasta bake </strong>with the <strong>oven-roasted</strong> <strong>courgette batons </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the<strong> remaining lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
